SATs Topics

How this works

These booklets contain every SATs exam question from past papers, sorted by topic to help you practise in a more focused way.

These booklets are designed to build confidence by showing that with the right approach, even the hardest questions become manageable.

    Key points:

  • The questions are arranged in order of difficulty, starting with the earlier (easier) ones and gradually getting harder.
  • You'll see topics split into numbered sections (e.g. Arithmetic 1, Arithmetic 2). Each section contains a small set of questions to complete.
  • I recommend ticking the box once you've completed a section - if possible, use a non-private browsing mode so your progress is saved automatically.
  • There's no pressure to finish everything - just pick the topics you feel need the most practice or try a little from each section.
